spirit:modelParameter.spirit:name: C_S_AXI_ACLK_FREQ_HZ
spirit:modelParameter.spirit:displayName: C S Axi Aclk Freq Hz

spirit:modelParameter.spirit:name: C_SCL_INERTIAL_DELAY
spirit:modelParameter.spirit:displayName: SCL Inertial delay filter value (in AXI clocks)

spirit:modelParameter.spirit:name: C_SDA_INERTIAL_DELAY
spirit:modelParameter.spirit:displayName: SDA Inertial delay value (in AXI clocks)

spirit:parameter.spirit:name: C_SDA_LEVEL
spirit:parameter.spirit:description: This parameter is used during transmit throttling when the AXI IIC acts as master transmitter.

spirit:parameter.spirit:name: TEN_BIT_ADR
spirit:parameter.spirit:description: This parameter enables or disables the 10-bit addressing mode. Logic resource savings result when 10-bit addressing is disabled

spirit:parameter.spirit:name: AXI_ACLK_FREQ_MHZ
spirit:parameter.spirit:description: This parameter specifies (but does not set) the frequency of the AXI4-Lite interface.

spirit:parameter.spirit:name: C_GPO_WIDTH
spirit:parameter.spirit:description: This parameter sets the width of the general purpose output vector. If the user does not connect anything to this port, then logic optimization removes any resources associated with it.

spirit:parameter.spirit:name: C_SCL_INERTIAL_DELAY
spirit:parameter.spirit:description: This parameter specifies the number of S_AXI_ACLK cycles used to define the width of the pulse rejection on SCL signals

spirit:parameter.spirit:name: C_SDA_INERTIAL_DELAY
spirit:parameter.spirit:description: This parameter specify the number of S_AXI_ACLK cycles used to define the width of the pulse rejection on SDA signals

spirit:parameter.spirit:name: IIC_FREQ_KHZ
spirit:parameter.spirit:description: This parameter determines the approximate frequency of the master mode generated SCL clock signal (Hz)
